## Feature: Vertical Cursor Line in div[role="presentation"]

**Trigger:** Popup checkbox control  
**Scope:** /resourcing pages only (case-insensitive URL match)  
**Control:** Checkbox (default = checked)  

**Behavior:**
- When enabled: Injects cursor-line-on.js to attach mouse tracking
- When disabled: Injects cursor-line-off.js to remove mouse tracking and cleanup
- Shows 2px red vertical line (24px tall) centered on cursor when hovering inside `div[role="presentation"]`
- Setting persisted via chrome.storage.sync

**Visual Specifications:**
- Line color: Red
- Line width: 2px
- Line height: 24px
- Position: Centered on cursor
- Visibility: Only when hovering inside target elements

**Cleanup Requirements:**
- Removes event listeners when disabled
- Removes any existing cursor line elements
- No memory leaks or orphaned elements